## Step 8: Monitoring with Gatus

Gatus provides two-tier health monitoring: a primary instance on the prod VLAN
monitors all services, and a sentinel on the NAS monitors the primary.

### 8.1 Prerequisites

- [ ] DNS record `gatus.{{ environments.prod.dns_domain }}` exists pointing to `{{ vms.gatus.ip }}`
- [ ] DHCP reservation for Gatus: MAC `{{ vms.gatus.mac }}` → `{{ vms.gatus.ip }}`
- [ ] SMTP relay accessible at `{{ email.smtp_host }}:{{ email.smtp_port }}`

### 8.2 Build and Deploy Gatus

```bash
# Build the Gatus image
framework/scripts/build-image.sh site/nix/hosts/gatus.nix gatus

# Generate Gatus config from config.yaml
mkdir -p site/gatus
framework/scripts/generate-gatus-config.sh > site/gatus/config.yaml

# Deploy (first time from workstation)
cd site/tofu
framework/scripts/tofu-wrapper.sh apply -target=module.gatus
```

Wait for Gatus to boot and obtain its TLS certificate (~1–2 minutes).

- [ ] Gatus VM deployed at `{{ vms.gatus.ip }}`
- [ ] Gatus API accessible: `curl http://{{ vms.gatus.ip }}:8080/api/v1/endpoints/statuses`

### 8.3 Verify Health Checks

Open the Gatus web UI in a browser at `http://{{ vms.gatus.ip }}:8080`.

All endpoints should show green except the sentinel (not yet deployed):
- [ ] DNS: dns1-prod, dns2-prod
- [ ] Vault: vault-prod
- [ ] Certificates: vault, gitlab
- [ ] PBS: reachable
- [ ] GitLab: API responds
- [ ] Proxmox nodes: all reachable
- [ ] Replication: health endpoints respond
- [ ] NAS: reachable

### 8.4 Deploy Sentinel on NAS

```bash
framework/scripts/configure-sentinel-gatus.sh
```

Verify:
```bash
ssh {{ nas.ssh_user }}@{{ nas.ip }} docker logs gatus-sentinel --tail 20
```

After the sentinel is running, the primary Gatus should show the sentinel
health check as green (it was red before).

- [ ] Sentinel running on NAS at `{{ nas.ip }}:8080`
- [ ] Primary shows sentinel health check as green

### 8.5 Test Alert Delivery

```bash
# Stop dns2-prod temporarily
ssh root@<node> qm stop <dns2-prod-vmid>

# Wait 2–3 minutes for Gatus to detect failure
# Verify email alert received

# Restart dns2-prod
ssh root@<node> qm start <dns2-prod-vmid>

# Verify recovery email received
```

- [ ] Failure alert email received
- [ ] Recovery alert email received

### 8.6 Test Sentinel

Stop the primary Gatus or block the sentinel's access to it. The sentinel
should send an email alert within 2–3 minutes.

- [ ] Sentinel detects primary Gatus failure
- [ ] Sentinel sends alert email

